ZH: 我们应该信赖自己的能力。
EN: We should have confidence in our abilities.

ZH: 他是一个很值得信赖的人。
EN: He is a very trustworthy person.

ZH: 她从来不轻易信赖别人。
EN: She never easily trusts others.

ZH: 在这个领域，我们需要信赖专家的建议。
EN: In this field, we need to rely on the advice of experts.

ZH: 家人是我们最值得信赖的支持者。
EN: Family is our most reliable support system.

ZH: 你值得信赖，我相信你会做出正确的决定。
EN: You are trustworthy, and I believe you will make the right decision.

ZH: 我们要建立一个互相信赖的合作关系。
EN: We need to establish a cooperative relationship based on mutual trust.

ZH: 他的诚实让人十分信赖。
EN: His honesty makes him highly trusted.

ZH: 老师忠实地信赖学生们的努力。
EN: The teacher firmly trusts the students' efforts.

ZH: 他长期以来一直令人信赖的朋友之一。
EN: He has been one of the most reliable friends for a long time.

ZH: 我们必须建立一个信赖和尊重的团队氛围。
EN: We must build a team atmosphere of trust and respect.

ZH: 我们相互之间建立了信赖关系，因此无需怀疑对方。
EN: We have established a relationship of trust with each other, so there is no need to doubt.

ZH: 友谊是建立在相互信赖和理解之上的。
EN: Friendship is built on mutual trust and understanding.

ZH: 客户必须信赖我们的产品质量。
EN: Customers must trust the quality of our products.

ZH: 在工作中，信赖是良好合作的基础。
EN: Trust is the foundation of good teamwork in the workplace.

ZH: 我们应该相互信赖，共同应对困难。
EN: We should trust each other and face difficulties together.

ZH: 建立信赖需要时间和努力。
EN: Building trust takes time and effort.

ZH: 我们需要一个能够信赖的建议者来帮助我们做出决策。
EN: We need a trusted advisor to help us make decisions.

ZH: 仔细选择值得信赖的伙伴很重要。
EN: It is important to carefully choose trustworthy partners.

ZH: 老板非常信赖我，将重要任务交给我完成。
EN: The boss trusts me very much and assigns important tasks to me.
